A man was gunned down in Paul Andrew Street near Crossroads in Gugulethu. CAPE TOWN - A man has been killed in an apparent hijacking in Gugulethu.The victim was gunned down in Paul Andrew Street on Monday.It's believed his car was later found in Nyanga, just hours later.The police s Frederick Van Wyk says: Circumstances surrounding a shooting incident on Monday at Paul Andrew Street near Crossroads in Gugulethu, whereby a 43-year-old man was fatally wounded, are under investigation. We ve opened a murder case for further investigation. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)